#How to Run-
1. Clone or download the repository
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/airline-dashboard.git
   cd airline-dashboard

2. (Optional) Create and activate a virtual environment
   python -m venv venv

   On Windows:
     venv\Scripts\activate

   On macOS/Linux:
     source venv/bin/activate

3. Install the required Python packages
   pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run the Flask web application
   python app.py

5. Open the app in your web browser
   http://localhost:5000          # Main dashboard
   http://localhost:5000/admin    # Admin panel for bookmarked routes

# Airline Booking Market Demand Dashboard

This is a Python Flask web app that visualizes and analyzes airline market demand data using interactive charts. It was built as part of a technical assessment for an internship opportunity.

## Features

- Search and filter airline routes by origin and destination
- Interactive charts for:
  - Route popularity (bar chart)
  - Price trends over time (line chart)
- Bookmark popular routes stored in SQLite database
- Admin panel to view bookmarked routes
- Modular code structure using Flask and Jinja2 templates

## Tech Stack

- Backend: Python, Flask
- Frontend: Bootstrap 5, Plotly
- Database: SQLite with SQLAlchemy ORM
- Visualization: Plotly Express


